# Car Online Sale System (COSS) – Functional Specification

## 1. Overview
The Car Online Sale System (COSS) is a web-based platform that allows users to buy and sell cars.  
It provides features for listing vehicles, searching cars, messaging sellers, and rating transactions.

The system focuses specifically on **vehicle trading**, unlike general marketplaces.

---

## 2. User Roles

### 2.1 Guest User
- Browse available cars
- Search and filter listings
- View car details
- Cannot contact sellers or post listings

### 2.2 Registered User
- Create and manage car listings
- Contact sellers via messaging
- Save favorite cars
- Rate and review sellers/buyers
- Mark cars as sold

---

## 3. Authentication & User Profile

### Features:
- Register (email/password)
- Login/logout
- Profile management:
  - Name
  - Profile picture
  - Location (important for car pickup)
  - Contact number

### Profile Display:
- User rating (stars)
- Number of reviews
- Active listings

---

## 4. Car Listing (Sell Feature)

### 4.1 Create Listing
Seller can add:

#### Basic Info:
- Title (e.g., "2007 BMW 325i")
- Price
- Location

#### Car Details:
- Make (BMW, Toyota, etc.)
- Model (325i, Corolla)
- Year
- Mileage (km)
- Fuel type (Petrol/Diesel/Electric)
- Transmission (Automatic/Manual)
- Condition (New/Used)

#### Additional Info:
- Description
- Upload multiple images
- Optional:
  - VIN number
  - Registration expiry
  - WOF status

#### Status:
- Available
- Sold

---

### 4.2 Manage Listing
- Edit listing
- Update price
- Delete listing
- Mark as "Sold"

---

## 5. Car Browsing & Search

### 5.1 Browse Cars
- View all available listings

### 5.2 Filters
Users can filter by:
- Price range
- Location
- Make & model
- Year range
- Mileage
- Fuel type
- Transmission

### 5.3 Search
- Keyword search (e.g., "BMW", "SUV")

---

## 6. Car Detail Page

Displays:
- Car images gallery
- Full specifications
- Price
- Seller information
- Location
- Listing status (Available / Sold)

### Actions:
- Message seller
- Save to favorites

---

## 7. Buying Flow

### Step 1: Find Car
User searches or browses

### Step 2: Contact Seller
- Click “Message Seller”
- Start conversation

### Step 3: Discussion
- Price negotiation
- Inspection arrangement
- Pickup/delivery

### Step 4: Mark as Sold
- Seller marks listing as "Sold"
- Listing becomes inactive

---

## 8. Messaging System

### Features:
- Chat between buyer and seller
- Linked to specific car listing

### Capabilities:
- Text messages
- Timestamp
- Conversation history

(Optional Advanced):
- Read receipts
- Notifications

---

## 9. Ratings & Reviews

### After Transaction:
Both users can:
- Rate (1–5 stars)
- Leave review

### Display:
- Average rating on profile
- Reviews visible publicly

---

## 10. Saved Cars (Favorites)

- Users can save cars
- View saved cars later
- Remove from favorites

---

## 11. Notifications (Optional)

- New message alerts
- Listing sold notification
- Price updates

---

## 12. Admin Panel (Recommended)

Admin can:
- Remove fake listings
- Ban users
- Moderate reviews

---

## 13. Database Structure (Basic)

### Users
- id
- name
- email
- password
- profile_image
- rating

### Cars (Listings)
- id
- user_id
- title
- make
- model
- year
- mileage
- fuel_type
- transmission
- price
- description
- status (available/sold)
- created_at

### Messages
- id
- sender_id
- receiver_id
- car_id
- message
- timestamp

### Reviews
- id
- reviewer_id
- reviewed_user_id
- rating
- comment

### Favorites
- id
- user_id
- car_id

---

## 14. Important Business Rules

- Only registered users can sell cars
- A sold car cannot be edited
- Users can only edit their own listings
- Ratings allowed only after interaction

---

